      </answers>
      <UID>6</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“The faithful don’t need judges to see into the hearts of fellow men.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“But they need guards to keep them from wandering into the upper districts?”</text>
          <def_link>6</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“Is it not said that justice is a joy to the godly, but terror to the evildoers?”</text>
          <def_link>8</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>7</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“Quite so, &lt;brother/sister&gt;,” smiles the guard. “The faithful can walk without fear for they are amongst brothers.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts>
        <string>rwd_reputation(GNZ_StairsGuard_01);</string>
      </onLoadScripts>
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“What can you tell me about the city?”</text>
          <def_link>9</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>8</UID>
    </dlgPart>
    <dlgPart>
      <portrait />
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>“The Magi built this hill to be closer to heaven, to be able to speak to the Gods and ask for their favor. Touched by their devotion, one of the Gods shed a tear which fell from the sky but didn’t hit the ground. It stopped in midair, frozen in time – a symbol of the Gods’ love and power.

“They say that Castle Ganezzar was built around this holy tear for to stand next to it is to stand in the presence of the divine.”</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>“It’s the most wondrous and holy relic, brother. I shall pray to be worthy enough to stand in front of it one day.”</text>
          <def_link>10</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear />
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>[lore success]“A tear? A tear in the fabric of our world?”</text>
          <def_link>11</def_link>
          <checkOnAppear>aod.lore &gt;= 5</checkOnAppear>
          <checksOnClick />
          <linksOnClick />
          <scriptsOnClick />
        </dlgAnsw>
      </answers>
      <UID>9</UID>
